# {{appName.pascal}}

Vite + React 19 + TypeScript SPA.

## Stack

- React 19, TypeScript ~5.7, Vite 6
{{#if hasTanstackRouter}}- TanStack Router (code-based routes in `src/router.tsx`)
{{/if}}{{#if hasReactRouter}}- React Router v7
{{/if}}{{#if hasTailwind}}- Tailwind CSS v4 (via `@tailwindcss/vite`)
{{/if}}{{#if hasApi}}- Typed `fetch` wrapper at `src/lib/api.ts`
{{/if}}{{#if hasSupabase}}- Supabase client at `src/lib/supabase.ts`
{{/if}}{{#if hasClerk}}- Clerk for auth
{{/if}}{{#if hasDocker}}- Docker (multi-stage build → nginx static serve)
{{/if}}
## Development

```bash
cp .env.example .env   # then fill in values
npm install
npm run dev            # starts on http://localhost:{{port}}
```

## Build

```bash
npm run build
npm run preview
```

## Type-check & lint

```bash
npm run typecheck
npm run lint
```

## Routes

| Path | Component |
|------|-----------|
{{#each routes}}| `{{path}}` | `{{componentName}}` (`src/routes/{{routeFile}}.tsx`) |
{{/each}}

Route files are **extension points** — generated once, then yours to edit. Regenerating the project will not overwrite them.
